> Installation of SP 3 is strongly recommended.
>
> SP 3 remedies existing issues in production and includes new functionality
> requests from the market.
> Functional enhancements to the platform include the introduction of a user
> preference to "Show best
> derived order" for all ICE spread markets, portfolio sort capabilities (by
> strip, by hub, alphabetical, etc.),
> and the ability to send messages to red orders.
>
> A full-scale enhanced client, version 7.37, will be listed along with SP 3
> and will be published to www.intcx.com
> under the "Downloads" link.  In addition, an API client (version 7.37)
> will be published to the same website
> location.  Release notes for SP 3 will be available from that site.
>
> To download The ICE client, follow the steps below:
>
> 1.) Go to the following site: www.intcx.com/index1.html and click on the
> link "Downloads"
> 2.) Enter your ID and Password in the fields provided.
> 3.) Under the heading: Production Environment...ICE Client...  click
> Install ICE p_7.37_s.exe.
>
> Note: Create an appropriate folder in your directory structure to prevent
> over-writing your current production
>  version, if applicable.  Follow the default settings.
>
> To apply The ICE patch, follow the steps below:
>
> 1.) Go to the following site: www.intcx.com/index1.html and click on the
> link "Downloads"
> 2.) Enter your ID and Password in the fields provided.
> 3.) Under the heading: Production Environment...ICE Client Patches...
> click Install
> 5.)  When the File Download window comes up please put the radio button in
> Save this file to disk and save it
> to your local hard drive or LAN.
> 6.)  Once saved, go to SP 3 (on your local drive or your LAN) and double
> click on the SP3.zip file (you will need
> to have WinZip on the local machine).
> 7.)  Extract these files to your C:\Program Files\INTCX\The ICE folder and
> overwrite the current files (you
> must overwrite the current files).
>
> Note:If your ICE folder is named differently than number 7 above,
> overwrite to the appropriate folder.
